&lt;p&gt;Advert&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you a student nurse or registered nurse with an interest in learning about careers in Haemodialysis nursing? The Royal London Hospital is currently recruiting for band 5 nurses within our Haemodialysis service.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Unit&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Bart’s Health is home to the UK’s largest renal &amp; haemodialysis unit, offering nurses the unique opportunity to work across a wide variety of clinical specialties and to advance their professional development. We offer a renal rotation programme across ward nursing, renal HDU and haemodialysis units. We can also offer the renal course in collaboration with London South Bank University.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our world class services include Medical, Surgical, Critical Care, Transplantation, Community Dialysis, Acute Dialysis, Research, Palliative Care, Renal Assessment, Living Donation, Acute Kidney Injury and Chronic Kidney Disease, based at our brand new hospital building near the City of London.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Education and Support&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have a dedicated education team to support you with your professional development and for student nurses, a comprehensive 18 month preceptorship programme which supports your transition from student to confident practitioner. You can take part in clinical workshops, e-learning modules, action learning and clinical competency assessments.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Sarah Mclean, Haemodialysis Senior Nurse, on Sarah.Mclean@bartshealth.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sarah Mclean, Haemodialysis Senior Nurse, on Sarah.Mclean@bartshealth.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
